TY  - JOUR
AB  - This paper presents a general equilibrium model in which all prices and quantities transacted are explicitly chosen by economic agents: there is no Walrasian auctioneer. Multiple equilibria occur with prices and wages taking their Walrasian values. Equilibrium quantities may also be Walrasian, or they may involve some price-taking workers being rationed in selling labor. This involuntary unemployment results from self-confirming expectations of inadequate effective demand, as in some interpretations of J. M. Keynes' ideas.
